<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36112e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36112e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36112e"> 112(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> blue mouldy for want / of a bating</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The scenes of turbulence which gave <font color="green">[Donnybrook]</font> its notoriety, were enacted at the great fair, which was held annually on the green beside the Dodder. Everyone knows the story of the man, who said he was &ldquo;<mark>blue mouldy for want of a bating</mark>&rdquo; and trailed his coat through the fair, defying anyone to tread on the tail of it. <small> D.A. Chart, <a name="DACD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#DACD"><cite title="source">The Story of Dublin</cite></a> (1907) 335</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
